<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Christmas Eve">
  <data key="d0">Christmas Eve</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Christmas Eve is the evening or day before Christmas Day, noted as a significant moment in the text where Scrooge is visited by his nephew.&lt;SEP&gt;Christmas Eve is the day on which the events occur, highlighting the contrast between Scrooge and the festive spirit of others.&lt;SEP&gt;Christmas Eve describes the night of the celebrations, characterized by dancing, food, and joviality.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8bc1edd983869352d14cf0886a9175a7</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scrooge's Nephew">
  <data key="d0">Scrooge's Nephew</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Scrooge's Nephew is a cheerful character who contrasts Scrooge's attitude by promoting the spirit of Christmas.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge's Nephew is a character who values Christmas and tries to engage Scrooge in festive spirit, proposing dinners and expressing love.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge's Nephew is depicted as a joyful character who laughs heartily, bringing a sense of warmth and happiness to the scene.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge's nephew is a character who participates in games, brings joy to the family gathering, and contributes to Scrooge's change in perspective.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge's nephew is characterized by his infectious laughter and humorous nature, contrasting with his uncle's demeanor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91614df5cb74cbe5e109a338a82041e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Counting-House">
  <data key="d0">Counting-House</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Counting-House is Scrooge's workplace, described as a cold environment where he conducts his financial dealings.&lt;SEP&gt;The counting-house is the office where Scrooge conducts his business and employs Bob Cratchit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Frosty Rime">
  <data key="d0">Frosty Rime</data>
  <data key="d1">naturalphenomenon</data>
  <data key="d2">Frosty Rime refers to the icy layer that covers Scrooge's head, eyebrows, and chin, signifying his cold nature.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coal-Box">
  <data key="d0">Coal-Box</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The Coal-Box is an object in Scrooge's room that holds coal and is used to fuel the fires in the Counting-House.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74e2466de2f67fd710ef2f20c0a8d9e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scrooge's Niece">
  <data key="d0">Scrooge's Niece</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Scrooge's niece is a character who enjoys music and games, displaying a love for her family and a competitive spirit in activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge's niece is depicted as a pretty and jovial young woman with a strong opinion about her uncle Scrooge, revealing her character through interactions at gatherings.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980038</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Topper">
  <data key="d0">Topper</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Topper is a spirited character who participates actively in games and music, showcasing a playful nature during the Christmas gathering.&lt;SEP&gt;Topper is a character at the gathering who expresses humorous opinions and draws attention from Scrooge's niece's sisters.&lt;SEP&gt;Topper is a character who attends the gathering with Scrooge, contributing to the cheerful atmosphere of the party.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980039</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Merriment">
  <data key="d0">Merriment</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Merriment represents the joyful atmosphere among Scrooge's relatives, contrasting with Scrooge's isolated disposition.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980039</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dinner Gathering">
  <data key="d0">Dinner Gathering</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The dinner gathering is a social event where Scrooge's nephew and niece engage in laughter, music, and discussions about their uncle Scrooge.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980039</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Infection of Laughter">
  <data key="d0">Infection of Laughter</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The infection of laughter symbolizes how joy spreads among Scrooge's family during their time together.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980039</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scrooge's Niece's Sisters">
  <data key="d0">Scrooge's Niece's Sisters</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Scrooge's niece's sisters are depicted as participating in the dinner gathering and expressing opinions about their uncle Scrooge.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-773d0df1dd25c356f7b771d780583e09</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980039</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Project Gutenberg">
  <data key="d0">Project Gutenberg</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Project Gutenberg is a digital library offering free access to eBooks, including "A Christmas Carol" by Charles Dickens.&lt;SEP&gt;Project Gutenberg is an organization that provides free access to electronic works and promotes the distribution of texts not protected by U.S. copyright law.&lt;SEP&gt;Project Gutenberg is an organization that provides free access to eBooks and emphasizes the importance of copyright compliance and licensing for electronic works.&lt;SEP&gt;Project Gutenberg is a service that provides free access to electronic works and eBooks, aimed at promoting public domain literature.&lt;SEP&gt;Project Gutenberg is known for the free distribution of electronic works in various formats, supported by volunteers and donations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-194cd9680f4967f48bea89678f7ece21&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-af4ae173c561e4594c5aea96198cce9d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c51b3dc560b408cce12cdfe5c9c94f57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-85f77f5e3a9aba01133555a2d20e2fd8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
