<node id="Ignorance">
  <data key="d0">Ignorance</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Ignorance is the boy revealed by the Ghost, symbolizing societal neglect and the consequences of ignorance in humanity.&lt;SEP&gt;Ignorance is presented as a boy, symbolizing a societal issue that carries the warning of doom.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980040</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Want">
  <data key="d0">Want</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Want is the girl revealed by the Ghost, representing the plight of the destitute and the societal issues surrounding poverty.&lt;SEP&gt;Want is represented as a girl, highlighting another aspect of societal neglect and need.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e7637ff18c5ded77a68cce0a87883fad</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Phantom">
  <data key="d0">Phantom</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Phantom is a ghostly figure shrouded in black that approaches Scrooge and symbolizes the fear of the future.&lt;SEP&gt;The Phantom represents a supernatural figure guiding Scrooge through his recollections and future considerations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Phantom serves as a guide for Scrooge, showing him potential futures based on his current behavior.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1a4fbcf1ed86864b9bfd5e8dba4c683&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="City">
  <data key="d0">City</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The City refers to the urban environment surrounding Scrooge, emphasizing the hustle and bustle unrelated to his personal journey.&lt;SEP&gt;City refers to the unspecified city in which Scrooge resides, representing a broader community context.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jacob Marley">
  <data key="d0">Jacob Marley</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jacob Marley is the deceased partner of Scrooge, who returns as a ghost to warn him about his life and choices.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is the deceased friend of Scrooge, whose spirit takes the form of the Ghost to warn Scrooge about the perils of his life choices.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is mentioned as the man whose intervention sends the messenger spirit to Scrooge.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a character who is referenced as being buried and plays a significant role in Scrooge's reflections on life and consequences.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a deceased character whose prediction influences Scrooge and frames the narrative's supernatural elements.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is the spirit of Scrooge's former business partner, representing a connection to the past and influencing Scrooge's change.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley is a character referenced in the story as a spirit who influences Scrooge's change of heart.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da2472b4ef2a535b62908f14d0fb0ca9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come">
  <data key="d0">The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">The Ghost of Christmas Yet to Come is the spirit that reveals future shadows to Scrooge, instilling fear and solemn dread.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Clerk">
  <data key="d0">The Clerk</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Clerk is an employee of Scrooge who exhibits a more positive attitude towards Christmas, attempting to show kindness despite Scrooge's demeanor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Marley">
  <data key="d0">Marley</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Marley is a deceased partner of Scrooge, whose death is emphasized as a critical aspect of the narrative.&lt;SEP&gt;Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner, remembered as having been a kindred spirit to Scrooge, although mentioned to have been dead for seven years.&lt;SEP&gt;Marley is Scrooge's deceased business partner, whose ghost appears to Scrooge, evoking memories and fear as he represents regret.&lt;SEP&gt;Marley is Scrooge's deceased partner, whose face appears to Scrooge in a surreal moment at the knocker.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980041</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Christmas Humour">
  <data key="d0">Christmas Humour</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Christmas Humour refers to the festive cheer associated with Christmas, which Scrooge dismisses as irrelevant.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="A Merry Christmas">
  <data key="d0">A Merry Christmas</data>
  <data key="d1">phrase</data>
  <data key="d2">A Merry Christmas is a common greeting associated with the festive season, which Scrooge sarcastically derides throughout the dialogue.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scrooge's Office">
  <data key="d0">Scrooge's Office</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Scrooge's Office is the setting for the dialogue where Scrooge interacts with his nephew and the gentlemen who come to ask for charity.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Portly Gentlemen">
  <data key="d0">The Portly Gentlemen</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Portly Gentlemen are characters who visit Scrooge in his office to solicit donations for the poor and destitute during the Christmas season.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Marley's Ghost">
  <data key="d0">Marley's Ghost</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">Marley's Ghost is a significant entity that symbolizes death and serves as a reminder of Marley’s past connection with Scrooge.&lt;SEP&gt;Marley's Ghost is the spectral figure of Jacob Marley, appearing to Scrooge with chains and a ghostly presence to convey a message.&lt;SEP&gt;Marley's Ghost is a spectral figure bound by chains, representing regret and the torment of unfulfilled deeds in life.&lt;SEP&gt;Marley's Ghost is an unearthly visitor that appears to Scrooge, causing him great disturbance and prompting reflections on his life.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7b10789a9cb0af6c553730b29bd9034&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cb661c37436355ccec2769b1d0350c5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Fireplace">
  <data key="d0">Fireplace</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The fireplace is a setting element in the room where Scrooge interacts with Marley's Ghost, symbolizing warmth contrasted with the ghost's chill.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Toothpick">
  <data key="d0">Toothpick</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">A toothpick is mentioned by Scrooge as a diversionary object during his tense encounter with Marley's Ghost.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1aa50206d02ed89418f65f97c6441d1c</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980042</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Scrooge's Ghost">
  <data key="d0">Scrooge's Ghost</data>
  <data key="d1">creature</data>
  <data key="d2">Scrooge's Ghost is the spectral figure appearing to Scrooge and is a manifestation of his fears and doubts during the encounter with Marley's Ghost.</data>
