<node id="Bob Cratchit">
  <data key="d0">Bob Cratchit</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Bob Cratchit is a character from Charles Dickens' novella "A Christmas Carol," where he serves as the overworked and underpaid clerk to Ebenezer Scrooge. His character embodies the hardships and struggles faced by the poor during the Victorian era. Bob's eagerness for Christmas Eve off highlights his desire to celebrate the holiday with his family, showcasing his dedication to both work and family life.

As the father of the Cratchit family, Bob is depicted as a hardworking man striving to support his loved ones on a limited income. He is characterized by his love for his children and his supportive nature, as seen when he expresses pride in his wife’s Christmas pudding. This reflects his caring disposition, despite the financial adversities he endures. Bob's relationship with his family is central to his character; he is not only a provider but also a nurturing figure who brings Tiny Tim, his ill son, home from church, indicating his emotional investment in his family’s well-being.

Throughout the story, Bob Cratchit demonstrates concern for his family while acknowledging the significance of Christmas, even in the face of Scrooge's dismissive attitude toward the holiday. His character symbolizes the resilience and compassion of the working class, as he maintains a cheerful and compassionate demeanor, despite the myriad of challenges the Cratchit family faces, including the looming specter of death that affects their lives. Bob's circumstances and those of his family, particularly Tiny Tim, further emphasize the theme of social injustice and the need for compassion and empathy among people, especially towards the less fortunate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-83ac129dc9b56f84c46760d153d68e93&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-94bea83e7153fc2064aa382b494936a1</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1765980058</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
