<node id="Mrs. Cratchit">
  <data key="d0">Mrs. Cratchit</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mrs. Cratchit is Bob Cratchit's wife in "A Christmas Carol," depicted as a loving mother and supporter of her family.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is Bob Cratchit’s wife, shown as industrious and caring, preparing for the family's Christmas dinner.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is the wife of Bob Cratchit and is proud of her cooking, especially the pudding she made for the family dinner.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is the mother of the Cratchit family, noted for her care and diligence in ensuring a festive Christmas dinner for her family.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is portrayed as a strong-willed character, expressing her true feelings about Scrooge passionately during the Christmas toast.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is a mother and wife, shown to care deeply for her family and manage household duties despite their struggles.&lt;SEP&gt;Mrs. Cratchit is a character who shows affection by kissing Bob and represents the caring nature of family in the narrative.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b0f459f5af1c3a5e0b92cbe4ee48b77b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e2e7ebcc19a53b399dc03aded4743e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1d4b58de5429cd1261370c231c8673e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-503f0bfa5453467c7c61d160a3540eca&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19d72c57ae3408758b18d2568e86dc6b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9e3921da66da5d761ab73cd849af6c43</data>
