<edge source="Jacob Marley" target="Scrooge">
  <data key="d7">5.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Scrooge implores Jacob Marley (the Ghost) for comfort and guidance concerning his existence and regrets.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge reflects on Jacob Marley, influencing his views on kindness and morality during the festive gathering.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley’s prediction influences Scrooge's encounters with the Spirit and the Phantom.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge's transformation is influenced by Jacob Marley, whose spirit encourages him to embrace Christmas and change his ways.&lt;SEP&gt;Jacob Marley's spirit influences Scrooge's understanding of redemption and change.</data>
  <data key="d9">influence,past influence,reflection,relationship,request for guidance,spiritual guidance,supernatural guidance,transformation,transformative experience</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-02baee20cc9463dbe08170a8e1043e32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-359187e7571bda4b0b08b2e0b6581e52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91572b3cd42786ba4cb2f180ca25cbf4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-90b95db5c53e4364a6bee36b7aa4d70f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43c9bee23adfa77aa9dedd22401bba7d</data>
