<edge source="Marley" target="Scrooge">
  <data key="d7">4.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Scrooge and Marley were partners in business, with Scrooge being the sole executor of Marley’s affairs after his death.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge recalls Marley as his business partner, whose spirit had a significant influence on his own character and past.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge encounters the Ghost of Marley, which induces fear and memories of his past.&lt;SEP&gt;Scrooge has a ghostly vision of Marley’s face on the knocker, highlighting his unresolved feelings about his deceased partner.</data>
  <data key="d9">business partnership,fear,haunting,legacy,partnership,remembrance,supernatural encounter</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-5dac41b3f9eeaf794f0147400b1718cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aac3484185ac66045df92214d245d5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89777b838d5447c7bd1ec11282c4ee89&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c43dac2fcd5b578242d907ea6f8fc7b</data>
